Indication in the context of respiratory conditions. 
 Polygala senega is indicated for cough (
 WHO, 2002; 
 ESCOP, 2003b). Other related indications include its actions as expectorant bronchitis, emphysema, and catarrh of the upper respiratory tract (
 Briggs, 1988; 
 WHO, 2002; 
 ESCOP, 2003b; 
 Lacaille-Dubois et al., 2020).
